# Part 8 ŌĆö Database Schema

Six tables support the workflow engine and standalone job scheduler. All use `InnoDB` with `utf8mb4` charset.

---

## Table Overview

| Table | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `workflows` | Workflow templates (name, description) |
| `workflow_steps` | Step definitions belonging to a workflow |
| `workflow_executions` | Live and historical execution records |
| `workflow_execution_steps` | Immutable per-step result log |
| `scheduled_jobs` | Job queue for one-time, recurring, and resume jobs |
| `job_results` | Per-attempt result log for scheduled jobs |

---

## `workflows`

The template table. One row per workflow definition.

```sql
CREATE TABLE `workflows` (
  `id`          int          NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `name`        varchar(100) NOT NULL,
  `description` text         DEFAULT NULL,
  `created_at`  datetime     DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  `updated_at`  datetime     DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`)
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8mb4 COLLATE=utf8mb4_unicode_ci;
```

| Column | Notes |
|--------|-------|
| `id` | Referenced by `workflow_steps.workflow_id` and `workflow_executions.workflow_id` |
| `name` | Max 100 chars. Required. |
| `description` | Optional free text. |

---

## `workflow_steps`

One row per step in a workflow. The `config` and `error_policy` columns are JSON ŌĆö the engine parses them in `loadWorkflowStep` before use.

```sql
CREATE TABLE `workflow_steps` (
  `id`           int                                          NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `workflow_id`  int                                          NOT NULL,
  `step_number`  int                                          NOT NULL,
  `type`         enum('webhook','internal_function','custom_code') NOT NULL,
  `config`       json                                         NOT NULL,
  `error_policy` json                                         DEFAULT NULL,
  `created_at`   datetime DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  `updated_at`   datetime DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`),
  UNIQUE KEY `uk_workflow_step` (`workflow_id`, `step_number`),
  KEY `idx_workflow` (`workflow_id`),
  CONSTRAINT `fk_workflow_steps_workflow`
    FOREIGN KEY (`workflow_id`) REFERENCES `workflows` (`id`) ON DELETE CASCADE
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8mb4 COLLATE=utf8mb4_unicode_ci;
```

| Column | Notes |
|--------|-------|
| `workflow_id` | FK ŌåÆ `workflows.id`. Cascades on delete ŌĆö deleting a workflow deletes all its steps. |
| `step_number` | Unique per workflow. The engine advances by incrementing this. |
| `type` | Determines how `config` is interpreted by `job_executor.js`. |
| `config` | JSON object. Shape depends on `type` ŌĆö see [03-internal-functions.md](03-internal-functions.md) and [04-variables-templating.md](04-variables-templating.md). |
| `error_policy` | Optional JSON. If `NULL`, defaults to `{ strategy: "ignore" }`. See [05-error-policies.md](05-error-policies.md). |

**`config` shape by type:**

```json
// webhook
{ "url": "https://...", "method": "POST", "headers": {}, "body": {}, "set_vars": {} }

// internal_function
{ "function_name": "send_sms", "params": {}, "set_vars": {} }

// custom_code
{ "code": "return input.x + 1;", "input": {} }
```

**`error_policy` shape:**
```json
{ "strategy": "retry_then_abort", "max_retries": 2, "backoff_seconds": 5 }
```

