## `workflow_executions`

One row per workflow run ŌĆö created when `POST /workflows/:id/start` is called. Variables are stored and updated here as the workflow progresses.

```sql
CREATE TABLE `workflow_executions` (
  `id`                   bigint NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `workflow_id`          int    NOT NULL,
  `status`               enum('pending','active','processing','delayed',
                              'completed','completed_with_errors','failed','cancelled')
                         DEFAULT 'pending',
  `init_data`            json   DEFAULT NULL,
  `variables`            json   DEFAULT NULL,
  `current_step_number`  int    DEFAULT '1',
  `steps_executed_count` int    DEFAULT '0',
  `created_at`           datetime DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  `updated_at`           datetime DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  `completed_at`         datetime DEFAULT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`),
  KEY `idx_workflow_status` (`workflow_id`, `status`),
  KEY `idx_status` (`status`),
  CONSTRAINT `fk_workflow_executions_workflow`
    FOREIGN KEY (`workflow_id`) REFERENCES `workflows` (`id`) ON DELETE RESTRICT
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8mb4 COLLATE=utf8mb4_unicode_ci;
```

| Column | Notes |
|--------|-------|
| `workflow_id` | FK ŌåÆ `workflows.id`. `RESTRICT` on delete ŌĆö you cannot delete a workflow that has executions. |
| `status` | See status lifecycle in [06-execution-lifecycle.md](06-execution-lifecycle.md). |
| `init_data` | Snapshot of the payload passed to `POST /start`. Never modified after creation. |
| `variables` | Live variable store ŌĆö merged after each step. `{{placeholders}}` resolve against this. |
| `current_step_number` | Set to `NULL` when execution completes. |
| `steps_executed_count` | Incremented after every step, including retried ones. |
| `completed_at` | Set when status reaches any terminal state (`completed`, `failed`, `cancelled`, etc.). |

**Status values:**

| Status | Set by |
|--------|--------|
| `pending` | Schema default ŌĆö not currently used by the engine (executions start as `active`) |
| `active` | Set at start and after resume |
| `processing` | Soft lock while `advanceWorkflow` is running |
| `delayed` | Set when a `wait_for` / `schedule_resume` step fires |
| `completed` | Terminal ŌĆö all steps finished, none failed |
| `completed_with_errors` | Terminal ŌĆö finished but one or more steps failed with `ignore` policy |
| `failed` | Terminal ŌĆö aborted by `abort` / `retry_then_abort` policy, or engine error |
| `cancelled` | Terminal ŌĆö manually cancelled via `POST /executions/:id/cancel` |

> ŌÜĀ’ĖÅ **Note:** `pending` exists in the enum but the engine never writes it ŌĆö executions are created directly as `active`. It may be useful for future pre-scheduled workflow starts.

