## `workflow_execution_steps`

Immutable append-only log. One row written per step execution by `recordStepResult`. Never updated after insert.

```sql
CREATE TABLE `workflow_execution_steps` (
  `id`                    bigint NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `workflow_execution_id` bigint NOT NULL,
  `step_number`           int    NOT NULL,
  `step_id`               int    NOT NULL,
  `status`                enum('success','failed','skipped','delayed') NOT NULL,
  `output_data`           json   DEFAULT NULL,
  `error_message`         text   DEFAULT NULL,
  `attempts`              int    DEFAULT '0',
  `duration_ms`           int    DEFAULT '0',
  `executed_at`           datetime DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`),
  KEY `idx_execution_step` (`workflow_execution_id`, `step_number`, `executed_at` DESC),
  KEY `idx_execution` (`workflow_execution_id`),
  CONSTRAINT `fk_wf_exec_steps_execution`
    FOREIGN KEY (`workflow_execution_id`) REFERENCES `workflow_executions` (`id`) ON DELETE CASCADE
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8mb4 COLLATE=utf8mb4_unicode_ci;
```

| Column | Notes |
|--------|-------|
| `workflow_execution_id` | FK ŌåÆ `workflow_executions.id`. Cascades on delete. |
| `step_number` | Copied from the step at execution time ŌĆö stable even if steps are reordered later. |
| `step_id` | FK to `workflow_steps.id` (no constraint defined ŌĆö soft reference). |
| `status` | `success` or `failed` are the two values the engine currently writes. |
| `output_data` | JSON output on success. `NULL` on failure. |
| `error_message` | Error string on failure. `NULL` on success. |
| `duration_ms` | Wall time from step start to completion including retries. |

> ŌÜĀ’ĖÅ **Note:** The schema defines `status` values `skipped` and `delayed` but the engine currently only writes `success` or `failed`. These are reserved for future use.
>
> ŌÜĀ’ĖÅ **Note:** The `attempts` column exists in the schema but `recordStepResult` does not currently write to it ŌĆö it will always be `0`. Retry count is tracked internally during step execution but not persisted here yet.

