## `scheduled_jobs`

The unified job queue. Used for standalone one-time and recurring jobs, and internally for `workflow_resume` jobs that wake up delayed executions.

```sql
CREATE TABLE `scheduled_jobs` (
  `id`                    bigint       NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `type`                  enum('one_time','recurring','workflow_resume') NOT NULL,
  `scheduled_time`        datetime     NOT NULL,
  `status`                enum('pending','running','completed','failed') DEFAULT 'pending',
  `name`                  varchar(200) DEFAULT NULL,
  `data`                  json         NOT NULL,
  `recurrence_rule`       varchar(100) DEFAULT NULL,
  `workflow_execution_id` bigint       DEFAULT NULL,
  `attempts`              int          DEFAULT '0',
  `max_attempts`          int          DEFAULT '3',
  `backoff_seconds`       int          DEFAULT '300',
  `execution_count`       int          NOT NULL DEFAULT '0',
  `idempotency_key`       varchar(100) DEFAULT NULL,
  `created_at`            datetime     DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  `updated_at`            datetime     DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`),
  KEY `idx_scheduled_pending` (`status`, `scheduled_time`)
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8mb4 COLLATE=utf8mb4_general_ci;
```

| Column | Notes |
|--------|-------|
| `type` | `one_time` / `recurring` for standalone jobs. `workflow_resume` created by the engine for delayed executions ŌĆö do not create these manually. |
| `scheduled_time` | When the job should next run. For recurring jobs, updated to the next occurrence after each run. |
| `data` | JSON payload. Shape varies by job type ŌĆö see [07-scheduled-jobs.md](07-scheduled-jobs.md). |
| `recurrence_rule` | Cron expression. Only used when `type = 'recurring'`. |
| `workflow_execution_id` | Set only for `workflow_resume` jobs ŌĆö used by the cancel endpoint to clean up pending resumes. No FK constraint. |
| `attempts` | Number of attempts made in the current execution cycle. Reset to `0` on reschedule for recurring jobs. |
| `max_attempts` | Per-job retry limit. Default 3. |
| `backoff_seconds` | Base for exponential backoff: `backoff_seconds ├Ś 2^(attempt-1)`. |
| `execution_count` | Total number of times this job has successfully completed across all cycles. |
| `idempotency_key` | Used for `workflow_resume` jobs ŌĆö prevents duplicate resumes for the same execution+step. Format: `resume-{executionId}-{stepNumber}`. |

> ŌÜĀ’ĖÅ **Note:** `workflow_execution_id` has no FK constraint ŌĆö deleting a `workflow_executions` row will not automatically clean up its pending `workflow_resume` jobs. The cancel endpoint handles this explicitly, but direct DB deletes will not.

**`data` JSON shape by type:**
```json
// webhook
{ "type": "webhook", "url": "https://...", "method": "POST", "headers": {}, "body": {} }

// internal_function
{ "type": "internal_function", "function_name": "send_sms", "params": {} }

// custom_code
{ "type": "custom_code", "code": "...", "input": {} }

// workflow_resume (engine-generated)
{ "nextStep": 4, "executionId": 42 }
```

