## `job_results`

Append-only attempt log for scheduled jobs. One row per attempt (not per job execution).

```sql
CREATE TABLE `job_results` (
  `id`               bigint NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `job_id`           bigint NOT NULL,
  `execution_number` int    NOT NULL,
  `attempt`          int    NOT NULL,
  `status`           enum('success','failed') NOT NULL,
  `output_data`      json   DEFAULT NULL,
  `error_message`    text   DEFAULT NULL,
  `duration_ms`      int    DEFAULT '0',
  `executed_at`      datetime DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`),
  KEY `idx_job` (`job_id`)
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8mb4 COLLATE=utf8mb4_general_ci;
```

| Column | Notes |
|--------|-------|
| `job_id` | FK to `scheduled_jobs.id` (no constraint ŌĆö soft reference). |
| `execution_number` | Which execution cycle this belongs to. For recurring jobs this increments each cycle. For one-time jobs it is always `1`. |
| `attempt` | Which attempt within that execution (1 = first try, 2 = first retry, etc.). |
| `status` | `success` or `failed`. |
| `output_data` | JSON response on success. `NULL` on failure. |
| `error_message` | Error string on failure. `NULL` on success. |
| `duration_ms` | Wall time from job start to completion. |

To get the full history for a job:
```sql
SELECT * FROM job_results WHERE job_id = ? ORDER BY execution_number DESC, attempt DESC;
```

